# Dotfiles / Chezmoi

My dotfiles are managed with [chezmoi](https://www.chezmoi.io/). The source repo is at `~/.local/share/chezmoi/`.

- When modifying config files that chezmoi manages (e.g. `~/.claude.json`, `~/.claude/settings.json`), always update the **chezmoi source** (the template/file under `~/.local/share/chezmoi/`) rather than editing the target file directly.
- After updating chezmoi source files, run `chezmoi apply --force` to apply changes.
- Files ending in `.tmpl` are Go templates — chezmoi renders them using data from `.chezmoidata.*` and `chezmoi.toml`.

# Code Quality

- **Verify types before proposing an approach.** Don't assume a property exists on a type — check the type definition first, especially at system boundaries.
- **Find existing patterns first.** Before designing new infrastructure, search for how the codebase already handles the analogous case. Match the existing pattern rather than inventing a new one.
- **Don't commit until the design is stable.** When a change touches multiple layers or involves uncertainty about how systems interact, work through the design questions before making incremental commits.
- **Push back when uncertain.** If you're not sure how a system behaves at a boundary, say so and propose verifying it before committing to an approach.

# Debugging

When diagnosing a feature that's broken in a codebase where an analogous feature works correctly:

- **Diff the broken surface against the working one first.** Structural comparison of JSX / props / wrapping components catches most bugs in minutes. Don't open library internals or propose config changes before doing this.
- **One theory at a time.** If a hypothesized fix doesn't change behavior, discard the whole theory — don't patch it with new assumptions. Stacked epicycles waste hours and accumulate broken state.
- **Verify fixes actually take effect before concluding "didn't work."** Vite HMR won't re-run app-init code like `createTabster`, `createRoot`, or singleton constructors captured in `useMemo`. Full reload may be required for the test to be valid.
- **Commit verified progress before trying the next thing.** Don't stack multi-theory broken state that's hard to untangle. Small forward increments keep options open.

