## Teams Notifications

Agents post status updates to Teams via `az rest` (Graph API). No MCP server needed.

- Team ID: `{{ .teams.teamId }}`
- Channel ID: `{{ .teams.channelId }}`

**Post a message:**
```bash
az rest --method POST \
  --url "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/teams/{{ .teams.teamId }}/channels/{{ .teams.channelId }}/messages" \
  --headers "Content-Type=application/json" \
  --body '{"body":{"contentType":"html","content":"<MESSAGE>"}}'
```

**Read recent messages:**
```bash
az rest --method GET \
  --url "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/teams/{{ .teams.teamId }}/channels/{{ .teams.channelId }}/messages?\$top=10"
```

## State File (~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md)

Tracks only what ADO doesn't know — local agent status, fitness, branches, PRs. ADO is the source of truth for everything else (priority, state, titles). Only the main cockpit session writes this file; agents never touch it.

```markdown
# Sprint State
- Sprint: <name>
- Sprint ID: <guid>
- Last Updated: <ISO timestamp>

## Work Items
| ID | Status | Fitness | Branch | PR | Notes |
|----|--------|---------|--------|----|-------|
```

**Status**: `queued` | `in-progress` | `done` | `blocked` | `skipped`
**Fitness** (agent readiness — assessed during `/work`):
- `ready` — Clear scope, agent can implement autonomously
- `investigate` — Needs root-cause analysis first; agent can research but not fix
- `needs-spec` — Requirements unclear, needs human planning first
- `needs-human` — Requires internal tooling/access an agent can't use

## Ad-hoc Work

All work — including ad-hoc tasks not from an existing sprint — follows the same cockpit conventions: correct ADO project/area/iteration from the config above, isolated worktrees for code changes, and state file updates. There is no "quick path" that bypasses these.

## Safety Rules
- NEVER modify, checkout, or force-push to any branch not prefixed with `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}`
- NEVER run destructive git commands (reset --hard, clean -f, etc.) outside of worktrees
- ALWAYS use isolated worktrees for implementation — agents create their own via `git worktree add` in the target repo
- Branch naming: `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}<workitem-id>-<short-description>`
- Only open DRAFT PRs — never publish or merge
- Never modify the user's current working tree or checked-out branch
- State file (~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md) and browser queue (~/cockpit/state/browser-queue/) are the ONLY mutable paths the cockpit session and agents write to (besides agent worktrees)
